; Test for issue #630 - Basis cost should follow commodities with lot pricing
;
; When using lot prices ({$150.00}), the --basis flag should report the
; cost basis (quantity * lot price), not the original commodity amount.
; Previously, --basis only worked with @ cost syntax, ignoring {} annotations.

2024/01/15 * Buy stock
    Assets:Brokerage       10 AAPL {$150.00}
    Assets:Checking

2024/02/15 * Buy more
    Assets:Brokerage        5 AAPL {$160.00}
    Assets:Checking

; --basis should show cost basis from lot prices ($2300 = 10*150 + 5*160)
test bal --basis --args-only --columns=80 -> 0
                   0  Assets
               $2300    Brokerage
              $-2300    Checking
--------------------
                   0
end test

; Register should also show cost basis
test reg --basis --args-only --columns=80
24-Jan-15 Buy stock             Assets:Brokerage              $1500        $1500
                                Assets:Checking              $-1500            0
24-Feb-15 Buy more              Assets:Brokerage               $800         $800
                                Assets:Checking               $-800            0
end test
